Sure, here is a C program to check if a number is a prime number:

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
  int n;
  printf("Enter a number: ");
  scanf("%d", &n);

  int flag = 1;
  for (int i = 2; i <= n / 2; i++) {
    if (n % i == 0) {
      flag = 0;
      break;
    }
  }

  if (flag == 1) {
    printf("%d is a prime number.\n", n);
  } else {
    printf("%d is not a prime number.\n", n);
  }

  return 0;
}
```

This program works by first getting a number from the user. Then, it iterates through all of the numbers from 2 to n / 2. If the number is divisible by any of these numbers, then it is not a prime number. If the number is not divisible by any of these numbers, then it is a prime number.

